fulltitle: History of US Militarism / Anti-War Activism in Rural America with Sanford Kelson
title: History of US Militarism / Anti-War Activism in Rural America with Sanford Kelson
_filename: _History of US Militarism _ Anti-War Activism in Rural America with Sanford Kelson.mp4
description:
Sanford Kelson is lawyer and anti-war activist in conservative, rural Pennsylvania and a former national President of Veterans For Peace. We discuss Ken Burns' 'The Vietnam War', the history of US militarism, and some of Sandy's experiences doing anti-war activism in rural America.

For more related content, please visit: https://archive.org/details/@altviewstv-fanclub
